  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>halloumi</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>pieces, lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced halloumi</strong> to a large bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>peri-peri spice mix </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up then set aside for later – this is your <strong>marinated halloumi</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681818024224-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681818024224-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681818024224-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681818024224-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681818024224-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the halloumi is marinating, peel and grate (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> </strong>roughly</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid on a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) with the<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681818028973-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681818028973-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681818028973-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681818028973-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681818028973-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong>, <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>spiced rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
