    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> marinated halloumi </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until the halloumi is browned – this is your <strong>peri-peri halloumi</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p>",
